    "description": "Heals the target a large amount of HP. The amount changes with the magic level and level of the user.\nMost frequently, players use this rune on themselves, but it can also be used to rescue a fellow player or a [[summon Creature|summoned creature]] from dying.<br />[[Druid]]s or [[Sorcerer]]s using this rune on themselves are guaranteed to heal completely because their magic power is a lot higher and their maximum [[HP|hit points]] are much lower than [[knight]]s or [[paladin]]s of equal level.<br />\n\nPrior to the Christmas Update of 2007, this rune was widely used by knights, however, after the update they are not longer useful for knights or paladins.\n\nThis rune can be used by mages to heal themselves or their blocker. [[Ultimate Healing Rune (Item)]] is by average around 5% weaker than [[Heal Friend]] (at higher levels difference is near 4%). The biggest advantage of this rune is that it has the highest minimal healing, making it the safest healing in critical fights. For example, if you heal your blocker with two very weak [[heal friend]] spells in a row which may not be enough to keep blocker alive, this rune have higher minimal healing which may be safer and less luck-based healing. Keep in mind, using this rune shares cooldown with other runes and potions.\n\nFor the spell, see [[Ultimate Healing Rune]].",
